<dl id="n12149d"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n12" href="#n12149d">N12 (VI.B.14)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n12all.htm#n12149d"> 149(d)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> S. Vincent F / rules of brothel</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Il n&apos;h&eacute;sitait pas &agrave; travailler lui-m&ecirc;me &agrave; des besognes qui nous para&icirc;traient un peu risqu&eacute;es. De vieilles traditions assurent qu&apos;il r&eacute;glementait les statuts de maisons de tol&eacute;rance. En maints endroits, il r&eacute;forma les moeurs. On vit donc des villes enti&egrave;res, comme Perpignan &agrave; la suite de sa pr&eacute;dication de 1415, o&ugrave; toute la population, y compris les &eacute;tudiants, v&eacute;cut d&apos;une vie sans taches. <br><font color="green">[[Saint Vincent Ferrier]</font> did not hesitate to tackle issues that for us would seem a bit risqu&eacute;. Old traditions claim that <mark>he regulated the rules of conduct in brothels</mark>. In many places he reformed morality. We can see entire cities, like Perpigan following his preaching in 1415, where the whole population, including the students, began to lead a spotless life.] <small> Matthieu-Maxime Gorce, <a name="STVF" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#STVF"><cite title="source">Saint Vincent Ferrier</cite></a> (1924) 171</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
